# Keep the Docker build context to exactly what the build needs:
# go.mod/go.sum, source trees (cmd/, internal/, migrations/ — embedded).
#
# Why each exclusion matters:
#   bin/   — local build outputs (50+ MB stale binaries) bust the COPY . .
#            source-layer cache on every build.
#   tmp/   — scratch outputs / dumps; large and irrelevant.
#   .env*  — gitignored but otherwise NOT dockerignored: a developer's .env
#            would be copied into the intermediate builder layer, a
#            secrets-into-layer hazard if build cache is ever exported or
#            pushed. (.env.example is excluded too; the image never reads it.)
#   .git   — history is not needed; VERSION/COMMIT come in as build args.
#   docs/  — specs and notes; pure cache-busting noise for the builder.

bin/
tmp/
.env*
.git
.gitignore
docs/

# Tooling/metadata never consumed by `go build` inside the container.
.claude/
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
compose.yaml
Makefile
README.md
